               Death
            ).

(The butter boat and taper candlestick deposed to by
Isaac Estridge
).

I am a Manchester warehouseman , I live in Friday-street , we have two doors, the door was open to Friday-street, on the first of April, between twelve and one, I was in the counting-house, when you come in at Friday-street door, this counting-house is to the left hand in the other corner;
William Whittenburg
was in the warehouse at a desk, I heard a noise in the warehouse, I was opening the letters at the desk, I apprehended that something was the matter, and ran from the desk immediately.
